  "market_context": "EUR/USD and GBP/USD are being compared side-by-side on the 1-hour timeframe. Both pairs are pulling into prior lows after a decline, providing an opportunity to spot SMT divergence between the correlated forex pairs before an anticipated reversal higher.",
  "key_observation": "At the first low, EUR/USD made a lower low while GBP/USD made a higher low — an SMT divergence. A second SMT then formed where GBP/USD made a lower low but EUR/USD made a higher low, stacking confirmation before displacement higher.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Compare structure of EUR/USD and GBP/USD at the recent low and identify that EUR/USD made a lower low while GBP/USD made a higher low — a first SMT divergence.",
    "Step 2: Refuse to long blindly on the SMT alone and wait for displacement or structural alignment to confirm the reversal.",
    "Step 3: Observe an aggressive move lower that takes out a secondary low on GBP/USD but not on EUR/USD, creating a second stacked SMT divergence.",
    "Step 4: Wait for displacement higher and identify the low-high-lower low-higher high breaker block sequence formed by the up-close candles.",
    "Step 5: Plan a unicorn entry on the breaker block with stop placed below the breaker and the fair value gap.",
    "Step 6: Set the target on the failure swings above for a 3.2R reward.",
    "Step 7: Price taps the breaker, sweeps, then displaces higher with down-close candles being closed through, supporting price upward into the take-profit."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit take profit for 3.2R",
  "lessons": "Don't long blindly on SMT alone — wait for structural confirmation (displacement, breaker block formation) and pair the divergence with a defined POI like a breaker/FVG unicorn for a high-probability entry with clear risk and target.",
